<paragraph id="8BE4407AFF8FFFEC1F7A947BFEA94860" blockId="3.[94,341,794,819]" box="[94,341,794,819]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis id="B92F9C68FF8FFFEC1F7A947BFEA94860" bold="true" box="[94,341,794,819]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Original Description:</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE4407AFF8FFFEC1FA0943BFE6C4E60" blockId="3.[94,719,858,1331]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
“Albido-testacea, dense sericea, capite supra foveolis et callolis partis anticae pronoti, disco pectoris dorsoque abdominis obscure fuscis vel piceis;capite subrotundato, utrimque impresso, carina antice et postice obsoleta instructo; fronte flavida, transversim testáceo-striata, convexa, distincte carinata; antennis fuscescentibus; pronoto carina obsoleta, antice et postice evanescente,instructo; scutello medio leviter impresso, ad basin interdum fusco; tegminibus dense sericeis, apice semicirculariter rotundatis; alis hyalinis, venis limboque fuscescentibus; dorso abdominis basi apiceque flavescenti; ventre dilute fusco, obsolete testáceo-fasciato, segmento terminali flavido; pedibus flavido-testaceis, tarsis obscurioribus, spina basali tibiarum posticarum parva. Long. corp. 7 
<superScript id="7C2EED32FF8FFFEC1D839398FD4F4E5B" attach="none" box="[679,691,1273,1288]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">½</superScript>
-8, tegm. 7-8; lat. Pron. 2 
<superScript id="7C2EED32FF8FFFEC1E639278FEAF4E7B" attach="left" box="[327,339,1305,1320]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">½</superScript>
mm”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE4407AFF8FFFEC1F7A923BFF174E20" blockId="3.[94,235,1370,1395]" box="[94,235,1370,1395]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis id="B92F9C68FF8FFFEC1F7A923BFF174E20" bold="true" box="[94,235,1370,1395]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Translation:</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE4407AFF8FFFEC1FA092FBFDE44C00" blockId="3.[94,719,1434,1875]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Light brown, opaque, surface of the head with foveas and even tubercle in the anterior part of the pronotum; ventral surface of the thorax light brown or dark; subrounded head, punctate on each side, vertex with weak carina; yellow frons, convex, with a strong carina and striated laterally; darkened antennae; pronotum with weak carena and obsolet in the anterior part; scutellum slightly punctured, darkened at base; tegmina opaque, apex rounded; wings hyaline, veins darkened; dorsal surface at base and apex of the abdomen yellowish, ventral surface light brown with darkened bands, terminal segment yellow; legs yellowish-brown, tarsi darkened, posterior basal spine of the tibia small. Body length: 7 
<superScript id="7C2EED32FF8FFFEC1D669078FDB24C7B" attach="none" box="[578,590,1817,1832]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">½</superScript>
- 
<quantity id="4CA3ED9FFF8FFFEC1D72907BFD644C60" box="[598,664,1818,1843]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
; tegmina: 
<quantity id="4CA3ED9FFF8FFFEC1F86905BFF064C00" box="[162,250,1850,1875]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" unit="mm" value="7.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="7.0">7-8 mm</quantity>
; pronotum width: 2 
<superScript id="7C2EED32FF8FFFEC1EF79058FE234C1B" attach="left" box="[467,479,1849,1864]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">½</superScript>
mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34113F1FF8FFFEC1F7A901BFC224A40" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE4407AFF8FFFEC1F7A901BFD824300" blockId="3.[94,719,1914,2131]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis id="B92F9C68FF8FFFEC1F7A901BFF314CC0" bold="true" box="[94,205,1914,1939]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Remarks:</emphasis>
Both the specimens were labelled as “typus” by Berg and mentioned as 
<typeStatus id="54E0FED8FF8FFFEC1EE390FBFDD64CE0" box="[455,554,1946,1971]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">syntypes</typeStatus>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCA3D8BFF8FFFEC1D7090FBFEE14C80" author="Carvalho, G. S. &amp; Webb, M." pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refId="ref5702" refString="Carvalho, G. S. &amp; Webb, M. 2005. Cercopid Spittle Bugs of the New World (Hemiptera, Auchenorrhyncha, Cercopidae. Sofia-Moscow, Pensoft. 280 p. (Serie faunistica n. 49)." type="book" year="2005">Carvalho &amp; Webb (2005: 58)</bibRefCitation>
. This species was originally described as 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B3BF9FF8FFFEC1FA490BBFE514CA0" authority="Amyot &amp; Serville" authorityName="Amyot &amp; Serville" box="[128,429,2010,2035]" class="Insecta" family="Cercopidae" genus="Tomaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92F9C68FF8FFFEC1FA490BBFF184CA0" box="[128,228,2010,2035]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Tomaspis</emphasis>
Amyot &amp; Serville
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCA3D8BFF8FFFEC1EF890BBFDA34CA0" author="Berg, C." box="[476,607,2010,2035]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="230 - 238" refId="ref5514" refString="Berg, C. 1879. Hemiptera Argentina. Enumeravit Speciesque Novas. Anales de la Sociedad Cientifica Argentina, 8: 230 - 238." type="journal article" year="1879">Berg (1879)</bibRefCitation>
and subsequently was synonymized with 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B3BF9FF8FFFEC1ED6909BFF3D4360" authority="(Germar)" baseAuthorityName="Germar" class="Insecta" family="Cercopidae" genus="Deois" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terrea" subGenus="Deois">
<emphasis id="B92F9C68FF8FFFEC1ED6909BFD324340" box="[498,718,2042,2067]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Deois (Deois) terrea</emphasis>
(Germar)
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCA3D8BFF8FFFEC1FC99F7BFE234360" author="Sakakibara, A. M." box="[237,479,2074,2099]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="9 - 30" refId="ref6642" refString="Sakakibara, A. M. 1979. Sobre algumas especies brasileiras de Deois Fennah, 1948 (Homoptera, Cercopidae). RevistaBrasileiradeBiologia, 39 (1): 9 - 30." type="journal article" year="1979">Sakakibara (1979: 12)</bibRefCitation>
. Are considered here as 
<typeStatus id="54E0FED8FF8FFFEC1F589F5BFF194300" box="[124,229,2106,2131]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">lectotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus id="54E0FED8FF8FFFEC1E3F9F5BFE4A4300" box="[283,438,2106,2131]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">paralectotype</typeStatus>
(ICZN, art. 74.1.1).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE4407AFF8FFFEC1C1B97BBFC224A40" blockId="3.[794,1417,218,275]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<typeStatus id="54E0FED8FF8FFFEC1C1B97BBFC244BA0" box="[831,984,218,243]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Paralectotype</typeStatus>
1733/2 lacks both mesothoracic legs and left forewing.
</paragraph>
